  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes </strong>and chop them into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender, then drain and set aside to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688738557674-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688738557674-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688738557674-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688738557674-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1688738557674-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, chop your <strong>parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1688738560477-x200.jpg",
